      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Source for Seeds</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Martha J Egan letter gives address for buying Mrs Burns's lemon basil, from Native Seeds Search in Tucson (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Mrs. Burns's lemon basil (Ocimum basilicum), referred to in ''Chocolate, Lemon, Clove: Yes, This Is Basil,'' June 28), was grown for many decades in Carlsbad, N.M., by the mother of Barney Burns, a board member of Native Seeds Search, which now sells her famous seeds. The company is at 526 North Fourth Avenue, Tucson, Ariz. 85705 (e-mail: info@Nativeseeds.org).  MARTHA J. EGAN  Corrales, N.M.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
